Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_665
Response Text: This question is a bit confusing because I’m not 100% which organizations or leaders that ACME supports and how. I do hope that ACME is able to amplify the voices and programming of Austin’s cultural centers and sites. When I first came to Austin a year or so ago it was very easy for me to find spaces like the Carver or Zilker. I would love to see our sites to have the budgets for updated advertisements, maps, merch, and on site reading materials. Maybe even some kind of brochure or bifold that helps unify the spaces based on which categories they fall into.

I also want to see how ACME can help protect/preserve the history and culture of Austin’s marginalized communities. It has been made clear that conversations about Black History, gender equality, or race in general are under attack. I want ACME to advocate for artists and creatives of marginalized communities, to save them from having to minimize their voices or their freedom of expression.

